cs.GT, cs.SI, cs.NI, cs.DS, cs.IT 

The paper deals with multi-player games and their dynamics, which are topics typically studied in the field of game theory (cs.GT). The use of simulation-based techniques to reason about the termination of dynamics suggests a connection to the field of simulation and modeling (cs.SI). The application of the framework to interdomain routing problems suggests a connection to the field of networking and internet architecture (cs.NI). The use of graph theory and preorders suggests a connection to the field of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the mention of improving outcomes w.r.t. the current strategy profile suggests a connection to the field of information theory (cs.IT).
